body:
> They don't want to put it in project README, because there will be no people left with full archive to sync from. They want to put the expense of storing all those terabytes of data on user's shoulders.


@AdminAnticaptcha This is irrelevant as erigon syncing is done through snapshots. 

That's the reason why you can wipe out the `chaindata` folder and keep the `snapshots` folder and it will reconstruct the `chaindata` without redownloading anything.
